  "texts": [
    "Different carbon sources produce important changes in metabolic phenotypes and, as a result, some genes that are essential in one condition source may be non-essential in another one.",
    "To test the predictive power of FlowGAT in other carbon sources beyond glucose, we trained the model using E. coli knock-out fitness data in ten other carbon sources that cover different entry points into central carbon metabolism 10.",
    "We built the corresponding mass flow graphs from wild type FBA solutions of the iML1515 model instanced to each carbon source.",
    "To build condition-dependent graphs, we constrained the flux of each nutrient exchange reaction to a fixed value (Supplementary Table 2).",
    "This resulted in 10 different MFGs that differ on their nodes and their edge weights."
  ],
